<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-189-848  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 189 848.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  April 17 1989 v6 n15 p134(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Chart notes. (glossary) (buyers guide)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McLusky, Catherine.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT/><TEXT>The chart beginning on Page 141 lists the manufacturers of LCD panels foroverhead projectors.andP;  All the information was supplied by the manufacturers.andM;Configuration, display, aspect ratio: Most panels for PC compatibles areconnected directly to the computer's video-output or graphics adapter, butsome are equipped with a special add-in board.andP;  All panels for use with theMacintosh 128, 512, Plus or SE require special adapters because these modelslack video-output ports.andP;  The aspect ratio is the ratio of screen width toheight.andM;Controls included: All of the products listed include contrast controls.andP;  Allunits capable of displaying color also offer color-selection controls,allowing the user to specify how the LCD panel will assign patterns or shadesof gray to the colors the computer screen displays.andP;  ''Image inversion''reverses dark and light areas on the display.andM;Maximum recommended wattage: To protect against overheating, somemanufacturers specify a maximum wattage for the lamp in the overheadprojector.andM;-- Chart compiledandM;by Catherine McLusky</TEXT></DOC>